Fortunatly, you're not "Most people".

05:31.440 --> 05:32.362
So for you, theres a chance to

05:32.480 --> 05:34.084
clear apart through the muck of the world

05:34.200 --> 05:37.204
And see ahead to the deep truth of things.

05:37.800 --> 05:39.484
Which is why we spent the last year

05:40.080 --> 05:43.084
strengthening your mind with the same tools

05:43.200 --> 05:45.771
used by some of the best brains in history.

05:46.880 --> 05:51.920
Descartes, Newton, Wittgenstein, to explore in the imagination

05:52.280 --> 05:55.204
what they were constraint from exploring in the physical world.

05:55.920 --> 05:59.242
Do we feel like recaping some of our favorite thought experiments?

06:01.040 --> 06:02.246
The infinite monkey theorem.

06:02.360 --> 06:03.327
The infinite monkey theorem...

06:03.440 --> 06:06.808
the classic way to wrap your head around the concept of "infinity".

06:06.960 --> 06:10.362
Which is so endless that if you put a monkey at a typewriter

06:10.680 --> 06:12.045
and let him bang away at it forever,

06:12.160 --> 06:17.644
he'll eventually, almost surely. Completly randomly type out the entire play of hamlet, word for word.

06:18.240 --> 06:21.210
I mean, the odds are nanoscale but he's gonna hit all the rights keys on a row

06:21.320 --> 06:24.324
on any given day, but over the strech of eternity

06:24.680 --> 06:26.091
across time, without any limit

06:26.200 --> 06:27.440
every event has some

06:27.560 --> 06:30.450
actual mathematical probabilty of really happening.

06:32.840 --> 06:33.762
Who else?

06:33.880 --> 06:35.006
I like the trolley problem.

06:35.880 --> 06:38.201
An out of control trolley car is speeding towards 5 people

06:38.320 --> 06:39.321
tied to a track

06:39.520 --> 06:41.045
but, you can pull a lever

06:41.760 --> 06:43.569
and make the trolley swerve into another track

06:45.360 --> 06:47.089
where only 1 person is going to get run down.

06:53.080 --> 06:54.081
Should you do it?

06:54.280 --> 06:56.203
If your being utilitarian about it, you can argue

06:56.320 --> 06:59.051
that you did the right thing letting 1 person die to save 5.

06:59.160 --> 07:00.571
But what if the situation was slightly different?

07:01.360 --> 07:03.647
This time there's no lever to make the trolley swerve

07:03.800 --> 07:06.690
but theres an obese man standing next to the track

07:06.800 --> 07:08.643
and you calculate that he wheights just enough

07:08.760 --> 07:09.761
to derail the trolley.

07:16.160 --> 07:17.241
Do you push him in front of it?

07:17.560 --> 07:18.800
Absolutly not!

07:19.080 --> 07:20.844
How's it less acceptable than the first version?

07:21.280 --> 07:23.248
You'r still sacrificing 1 person to save 5.

07:23.360 --> 07:24.407
They're both wrong.

07:26.440 --> 07:28.408
Don't be fool by the arithmetic

07:29.360 --> 07:31.488
it's murder, eithir way.

07:32.920 --> 07:33.842
Anyone else?

07:33.960 --> 07:35.450
The ignorant bliss paradox.

07:36.840 --> 07:39.411
You're hanging off the highest tower in Yakarta

07:39.920 --> 07:41.809
it's a thousand foot drop to your death

07:41.920 --> 07:43.922
so you call your three best friends for help

07:46.000 --> 07:47.206
they rush out to save you

07:47.920 --> 07:51.891
but they're afraid if they try to pull you up, they might be yanked over themselves

07:52.000 --> 07:53.001
so they step back.

07:57.160 --> 08:02.303
You fall...

08:02.403 --> 08:03.703
and live.

08:03.840 --> 08:06.571
But do you wish you never tested your friends, in the first place?

08:06.880 --> 08:08.325
Since now you know you can't count on them

08:08.440 --> 08:10.169
when it's a matter of life or death.

08:10.280 --> 08:13.284
Would it be better if you stayed ignorant of what their truly good for

08:13.400 --> 08:15.004
and gone on being friend forever?

08:15.200 --> 08:16.247
I'd wanna know the truth

08:16.960 --> 08:20.043
cut your loses, and walk on. you'll find other friends.

08:20.320 --> 08:22.049
You'll fall off other towers.

08:22.320 --> 08:23.526
The good news is:

08:24.320 --> 08:26.129
although we're about to part ways.

08:27.160 --> 08:32.006
Not one of you leaves here, lacking the credentials to thrive in the world

08:33.080 --> 08:36.482
your all well equipped, to push on to university

08:37.280 --> 08:40.124
and become happy, energetic members

08:40.240 --> 08:43.801
of a post industrial twenty-first century society.

08:48.280 --> 08:53.241
On the other hand. what if that society ceases to exist?

08:54.400 --> 08:57.210
What if your credentials don't mean what you expected?

08:57.520 --> 09:01.081
And your expectations mean nothing at all?

09:01.960 --> 09:03.610
I know it's hard to concieve of everything

09:03.720 --> 09:07.122
you'ved based your plans on, being wiped away at a single stroke

09:07.520 --> 09:10.649
but I'ts happened before and it can happen again

09:15.600 --> 09:17.011
so let's say things do change

09:18.440 --> 09:21.842
I propose one last good ancan experiment

09:22.480 --> 09:25.882
a final thought experiment, for our final session together.

09:26.600 --> 09:28.762
Something on a grand scale, something juicy.

09:29.600 --> 09:32.888
Let's invision a global cataclysm

09:33.440 --> 09:35.727
in the event of which, how do you survive?

09:35.840 --> 09:39.208
Uh, the last day of the year is you know

09:39.320 --> 09:41.607
traditionally sort of a chill experience for seniors

09:42.120 --> 09:44.009
this is starting to feel, not so chill.

09:44.120 --> 09:47.761
Uh, the last day of the year is traditionally, you now

09:47.880 --> 09:50.724
still a day which I can fail seniors.

09:51.240 --> 09:52.765
Or at least knock them down a letter grade

09:52.880 --> 09:53.847
for refusing to participate.

09:53.960 --> 09:55.724
That's what the academic handbook says.

09:55.840 --> 09:58.127
But what kind of cataclysm are we talking about?

09:58.560 --> 10:01.723
Gamma ray burst, Pandemic, Erupting super volcano,

10:01.840 --> 10:04.764
a sudden shift in the earth axis rotation, gray goo?

10:04.880 --> 10:06.120
Hang on chips, we'll get there.

10:06.240 --> 10:10.211
But is it biological? geological? Thermal nuclear? Meteorological?

10:10.640 --> 10:14.087
Let's go old school, say Atomic.

10:16.080 --> 10:19.527
Ready? set.

10:22.280 --> 10:23.361
Think...

10:45.640 --> 10:47.847
Definetly radiological and heading this way.

10:48.000 --> 10:49.684
Sorry, what are we doing in Prambanan?

10:49.800 --> 10:50.801
Field trip.

10:50.960 --> 10:56.126
Listen up everyone. We're going to have to take shelter here in this reinforced bunker.

11:51.000 --> 11:52.001
You see the problem.

11:53.240 --> 11:56.005
We're a group of 21 but the bunker is only built for 10.

11:56.120 --> 11:59.408
So we'll share a beds and ration supplies.

12:00.520 --> 12:02.363
Can't be done. Let me show you why.

12:02.560 --> 12:07.009
You can't share oxygen, every cubic centimeter of breathable air in here

12:07.160 --> 12:10.642
once the outer door is seal, comes from these compressed tanks

12:11.040 --> 12:11.927
this place has been enginered

12:12.080 --> 12:14.048
to support 10 people for 1 year

12:14.280 --> 12:17.011
even 1 person more means, death by hypoxia.

12:17.240 --> 12:20.847
If you try to cram anyone else in, you'll asphyxiate.

13:00.080 --> 13:02.765
The temperature of an impact point is ten million degrees

13:03.000 --> 13:05.480
we have maybe an hour before the wind starts dropping fallout.

13:05.600 --> 13:07.728
This is a radiological event thats global in scope

13:08.000 --> 13:10.480
to live through it, we'll have to spend a full year inside this bunker

13:10.640 --> 13:13.564
which is equipped with a generator and fuel supply to keep it running that long

13:14.040 --> 13:15.644
which means you have to decide

13:15.760 --> 13:18.491
whos valuable enough to expend limited resources on.

13:19.040 --> 13:21.771
I stipulate the existance of 1,000 bunkers around the world

13:21.880 --> 13:25.566
times 10 occupants per bunker, that's a gene pool of 10,000 people

13:25.680 --> 13:27.284
to reboot the human race with.

13:27.400 --> 13:31.485
I'm sorry, are you saying we are suppose to choose who goes in the bunker and

13:32.200 --> 13:36.250
who stays out and dies? becouse if that's the experiment I'm not doing it.

13:36.680 --> 13:38.409
Well, you have to.

13:38.800 --> 13:40.962
I won't. It's repulsive.

13:41.840 --> 13:43.490
It's the sort of pseudo-science

13:43.600 --> 13:47.525
a gang of nazis would have dreamt up in a big garden, circa 1939.

13:47.680 --> 13:49.045
This isn't a eugenics experiment

13:49.680 --> 13:51.125
the goal isn't to improve the human race

13:51.240 --> 13:52.844
the goal is to save the human race.

13:53.600 --> 13:56.729
Which means, a commitment to reason no matter how much it hurts.

13:57.120 --> 13:58.167
I decline.

13:58.280 --> 14:00.760
Then we'll be 20 rather than 21 to whittle down to 10.

14:00.880 --> 14:03.008
When the hot particles of nuclear fallout

14:03.120 --> 14:08.684
burn through your skin and your organs start shutting down through radiation poisoning, ..

14:09.920 --> 14:11.331
Try not to scream.

14:16.080 --> 14:18.003
Well, I suppose I'm in.

14:18.320 --> 14:23.042
I'm sorry but this one is not for me, so...

14:31.200 --> 14:34.761
the thing about an A+, as far as semester grades go

14:35.600 --> 14:39.446
it's more than rare, it's practically mythological.

14:40.200 --> 14:45.969
And an A+ in philosophy, there's never been one in the history of this department.

14:46.560 --> 14:50.007
So I have to ask, How does it feel knowing

14:50.120 --> 14:54.330
you could've been the first, if only you hadn't walked out the door?

14:55.360 --> 14:58.284
Bribery is not my very favorite form of negotiation.

14:58.520 --> 14:59.567
Then what about sympathy?

15:00.080 --> 15:03.050
Let's say if you leave someone else pays.

15:03.480 --> 15:04.970
The difference between an A+ and an A

15:05.080 --> 15:09.563
won't change your life, but for example, james?

15:10.080 --> 15:12.048
A grade that drops form a B-to a c+

